You are only updating contributors. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the contributor property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating contributor in the description.

## "contributor" model
The contributor is a real world object that may be associated with multiple name strings. At least one name is required per contributor and the contributor should have a type.

| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| name | Names associated with a contributor. Contributor name types must be from the "contributor.name" controlled list and multipart name types must be from the "contributor.name.structuredValue" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| type | Entity type of the contributor (person, organization, etc.). Contributor types must be from the "contributor" controlled list. | String | No |
| status | Status of the contributor relative to other parallel contributors (e.g. the primary author among a group of contributors). Use "primary" to indicate preferred status. | String | No |
| role | Relationships of the contributor to the resource or to an event in its history. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| identifier | Identifiers and URIs associated with the contributor entity. Contributor identifier types must be from the "contributor.identifier" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| affiliation | Institutional or other affiliation associated with a contributor. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| note | Other information associated with the contributor. Contributor note types must be from the "contributor.note" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| valueAt | URL or other pointer to the location of the contributor information. | String | No |


### Basic contributor with name and contributor type

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Dorothy L. Sayers"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person"
    }
  ]
}
```

Contributor types must be from the "contributor" controlled list.

### Contributor names with name types

In addition to the contributor type, name values may have types as well to distinguish them from other names of the contributor.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Dorothy L. Sayers",
          "type": "display"
        },
        {
          "value": "Dorothy Leigh Sayers",
          "type": "alternative"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person"
    }
  ]
}
```

Contributor name types must be from the "contributor.name" controlled list.

### Multipart contributor name

A name may be split into component parts and each part given a type using structuredValue.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "structuredValue": [
            {
              "value": "Sayers",
              "type": "surname"
            },
            {
              "value": "Dorothy L.",
              "type": "forename"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "person"
    }
  ]
}
```

Contributor name part types must be from the "contributor.name.structuredValue" controlled list.

### Contributor with role

#### Single role

The role is associated with the contributor, not the name. See MARC relator terms for role terms, codes, and URIs.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Dorothy L. Sayers"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person",
      "role": [
        {
          "value": "author",
          "code": "aut",
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut",
          "source": {
            "code": "marcrelator"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Multiple roles

One contributor may have multiple roles.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Dorothy L. Sayers"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person",
      "role": [
        {
          "value": "author of introduction"
        },
        {
          "value": "editor"
        }
       ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Contributor or name with status

#### Contributor status

At the contributor level, a status of "primary" indicates that the contributor is the agent primarily responsible for the resource.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Dorothy L. Sayers"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person",
      "status": "primary"
    },
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Muriel St. Clare Byrne"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person"
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Contributor name status

At the name level, a status of "primary" indicates that the name is the preferred form for the contributor.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Sayers, Dorothy L.",
          "status": "primary"
        },
        {
          "value": "Sayers, Dorothy Leigh"
        }
      ],
      "type": "person"
    }
  ]
}
```

Status may be present at both levels.

### Contributor with affiliation

The affiliation is associated with the contributor as it is an attribute of the person or organization.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Sayers, Dorothy L."
        }
      ],
      "type": "person",
      "affiliation": [
        {
          "value": "Oxford University"
        }
       ]
     }
   ]
}
```

### Contributor with identifier

Identifiers for the agent as an entity, such as ORCID and Wikidata, are associated with the contributor.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Sayers, Dorothy L.",
          "type": "person",
          "identifier": [
            {
              "uri": "https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q106740",
              "source": {
                "code": "wikidata"
              }
            }
            ]
          }
       ]
     },
      {
        "name": [
          {
            "value": "Moulton, Mo",
            "type": "person",
            "identifier": [
              {
                "uri": "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7028-6233",
                "type": "ORCID"
              }
            ]
          }
   ]
      }
  ]
}
```

Contributor name part types must be from the "identifier" controlled list.

### Contributor with name authority

Identifiers for an authorized name string, such as LCNAF, are associated with the name. The entered name should match the authorized form. See name authority source codes.

```json
{
  "contributor": [
    {
      "name": [
        {
          "value": "Sayers, Dorothy L. (Dorothy Leigh), 1893-1957",
          "uri": "https://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79046044",
          "source": {
            "code": "naf"
          },
          "type": "person"
        }
       ]
     }
   ]
}
```

